<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1152,1334]" pageId="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,275,1191,1217]" pageId="21">Notes.</emphasis>
The single female specimen is predominantly dark bodied with yellow legs, the fore legs being missing. The thorax has three fused black stripes leaving the humeral area dark yellowish. The wings have a little more than the apical quarter dark brownish with a slight cloud at the base of r-m. The finding of males is necessary to establish its identity.
</paragraph>
